# S05-T11: Knowledge Slug + Instance Docs

## Objective
Use app-agent's own knowledge system; split agnostic vs per-app rules (invariant §6/§7).

## Execution
- Update `core/docs/knowledge/work-control.md` (the ONLY allowed core change): document the
  orchestrator spine, the agent-role taxonomy reference, WS contract, and the write-back +
  gate flow. Keep `// SEE: feature "work-control"` annotations on the new server routes.
- Add per-app instance docs under `apps/work-control/docs/` (or README section): how mock
  agents behave, layer→lead-role defaults, env (`CORE_DATASOURCE_*`), run instructions.
- Run `bun run feature:health` — `work-control` slug must be covered (no broken SEE refs).

## Out
`core/docs/knowledge/work-control.md`, `apps/work-control/docs/*`, README update

## Done when
- `feature:health` green for `work-control`; agnostic vs per-app docs clearly separated.
